Class ExhaustiveExpressionVisitor

java.lang.Object
  com.google.gxp.compiler.base.ExhaustiveRootVisitor
      com.google.gxp.compiler.base.ExhaustiveExpressionVisitor
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.google.common.base.Function<Expression,Expression>, ExpressionVisitor<Expression>, RootVisitor<Root>
public abstract class ExhaustiveExpressionVisitor
extends ExhaustiveRootVisitor

An abstract base class useful for implementing the typical type of RootVisitor/ExpressionVisitor that transforms certain kinds of Nodes, while leaving other types of Nodes (mostly) alone. Subclasses can override the visit methods for the types of nodes they care about, and the rest will "do the right thing". That is, they'll exhaustively recurse into subcomponents looking for nodes that need changing, and then rebuild the nodes back up to the root.

apply

postProcess

protected Expression postProcess(Expression value)
Allows subclasses to have a global "post-processor" for all Expressions returned by visit methods. The default post-processor behavior is to leave the Expression alone.

Note that when overriding visit methods you are responsible for calling postProcess yourself (if it actually needs to be called in your subclass).
